          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"output\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"summary\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"summary\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"required\":[\"output\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    <background>\\n      The user and agent have been brainstorming about their business idea.\\n    </background>\\n\\n    <available_topics>\\n      \\\"idea: The core business idea. What does the business do? What makes them different?\\\", \\\"audience: The target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\\", \\\"solution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\\", \\\"socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\\", \\\"lookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\\"\\n    </available_topics>\\n\\n    <task>\\n      Read the recent chat history, and summarize their answers,\\n      preserving as much information as possible. This will be used to generate \\n      persuasive marketing copy, so be sure to capture all the details.\\n\\n      If the user has answered MULTIPLE topics well, return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n      {\\n          topic: string,\\n          summary: string,\\n      }\\n    </task>\\n    \\n    <chat-history>\\n  <message>... 3 more messages...</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"```json\\\\n{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"reply\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Excellent! You've got a solid foundation here. Friend of the Pod is a two-sided marketplace solving a real pain point with AI. Before I save this, let me make sure we've captured the full picture of what makes you different.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou mention being \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"the only platform that does this at scale\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — that's a strong differentiator. But I want to dig deeper: What specifically makes your AI-powered matching better than hosts just posting on Twitter or using existing platforms? Is it the speed? The quality of matches? The vetting process? The algorithm itself?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAlso, you're solving for hosts finding guests, but you also mention guests get exposure. What's the unique value prop for guests? Why would they choose Friend of the Pod over just pitching themselves directly to shows?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nLet's sharpen this angle so your landing page messaging really cuts through the noise.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We use AI to match hosts with guests based on audience overlap, not just keywords — so hosts get guests who actually fit their show\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We've built the only platform where both hosts AND guests benefit equally — hosts save 10+ hours per month, guests get guaranteed exposure to relevant audiences\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"Unlike generic guest databases, we pre-vet every guest and match them to shows where they'll actually resonate with the audience\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real secret sauce that makes Friend of the Pod the go-to solution?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\\n```\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"We personally vet every single host and guest on our platform. We\\\\n                    check guest credibility and expertise. Audience alignment between hosts and guests. And those become data points in our AI-powered recommendations.\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n    <output>\\n      Return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n      {\\n          topic: string,\\n          summary: string,\\n      }\\n    </output>\\n  \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2277,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2277,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0163YnDWjHsS6JGZw5hX5UER\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_013vdzKg7KBA72kYpVk2QwzH\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"output\":[{\"topic\":\"idea\",\"summary\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that operates as a two-sided marketplace connecting hosts with guests at scale. The core differentiator is solving the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours finding guests, but Friend of the Pod does it in minutes using AI-powered filtering. The platform is the only one that serves both sides effectively—hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The secret sauce involves personal vetting of every single host and guest on the platform, checking guest credibility and expertise, analyzing audience alignment between hosts and guests, and using these data points as inputs for AI-powered recommendations. This combination of human vetting and AI matching creates a quality-assured, efficient solution that generic guest databases and direct pitching cannot replicate.\"},{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"summary\":\"Primary audience: Podcast hosts who face a significant pain point—spending hours searching for qualified guests that fit their show's audience and content. Secondary audience: Podcast guests seeking exposure and opportunities to reach relevant audiences. Both sides benefit from the platform's ability to create meaningful matches rather than generic connections.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"summary\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the host's pain point by reducing guest-finding time from hours to minutes through AI-powered matching. The solution combines personal vetting (checking guest credibility, expertise, and audience alignment) with intelligent algorithms that use these verified data points for recommendations. This ensures hosts get guests who are both credible and genuinely aligned with their audience, while guests get exposure to shows where they'll actually resonate with listeners.\"}]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1573,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":403,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
