        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1475,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1475,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0113eVtJRSTudv8eXqoyKCaK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! I've got a clear picture of your idea and audience. Now let's dig into the **solution** — this is where we really sell the value.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Here's the key question: How does Friend of the Pod specifically solve those pain points? Walk me through the concrete benefits and outcomes a podcast host experiences when they use your platform. What changes for them?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Instead of spending 10 hours per week sifting through spammy DMs, hosts spend 15 minutes setting up their preferences and get 5 perfectly matched guest recommendations\\\",\\n    \\\"Hosts go from feeling overwhelmed by low-quality pitches to having a curated pipeline of guests who are actually relevant to their audience\\\",\\n    \\\"The platform filters out 95% of the noise, so hosts only see guests that meet their specific criteria (topic, audience size, expertise level, etc.)\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Give me the real transformation that happens when a host uses Friend of the Pod. What's the before and after?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2622,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":249,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
