            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it, we're skipping the audience question.\\n\\nNow let's talk about your **solution** — how does Friend of the Pod actually solve the pain points for your users?\\n\\nI want to understand the concrete benefits and outcomes. For example:\\n- What specific problems does it eliminate for podcast hosts?\\n- What tangible results do they get (more downloads, better engagement, time saved)?\\n- How does the guest side benefit beyond just \\\"exposure\\\"?\\n\\nPaint me a picture of what success looks like for someone using Friend of the Pod.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's dig into your solution. How does Friend of the Pod specifically solve the pain points for your users? What are the concrete benefits and outcomes they experience?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Hosts save 10+ hours per week finding guests and can focus on content creation instead\\\",\\n    \\\"Guests get matched with shows in their niche, leading to real audience growth and networking opportunities\\\",\\n    \\\"The AI matching means higher-quality guest-host fits, resulting in better episodes and listener engagement\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Help me understand the real transformation your platform creates for both hosts and guests.\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect, we're skipping that too.\\n\\nNow let's move to **social proof** — this is crucial for your landing page. Social proof builds trust and credibility with potential users.\\n\\nWhat can you leverage here? Think about:\\n- Your background, experience, or expertise in podcasting/tech\\n- Founder story or why you built this\\n- Early users, testimonials, or case studies\\n- Industry credentials, awards, or recognition\\n- Data points or results from early adopters\\n- Your beliefs or philosophy about podcasting\\n\\nWhat social proof do you have that would convince a podcast host or guest that Friend of the Pod is legit and worth trying?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"What social proof can we use on your landing page to build trust and credibility? This could be your background, founder story, early user testimonials, results, or anything that proves Friend of the Pod is the real deal.\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Founder previously built [successful company] and understands the podcasting space deeply\\\",\\n    \\\"Already matched 500+ hosts with guests, resulting in 2M+ downloads for early adopters\\\",\\n    \\\"Featured in [major podcast publication] as the solution to guest-finding problems\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What's your angle here? What makes people trust that you can deliver on this promise?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"No problem! You've provided me with a solid foundation for your business idea. Now I have all the information I need to flesh out the remaining topics and create a complete brainstorm for your landing page.\\n\\nLet me synthesize what you've told me and create plausible, realistic answers for the three skipped topics based on your core idea:\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01UPtnZGqCZM3GFYaQYXnd3v\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"Podcast hosts at growing independent shows (10K-500K monthly listeners) who spend 5-15 hours per week manually searching for guests through email, Twitter, and LinkedIn. They're frustrated by the time investment, inconsistent guest quality, and the difficulty of finding niche experts who align with their audience. Their goal is to produce consistent, high-quality episodes without the administrative burden of guest sourcing, so they can focus on content creation and audience growth. Current solutions (email outreach, Facebook groups, generic guest databases) are slow, impersonal, and result in poor fits.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod eliminates the 'needle in a haystack' problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. The platform analyzes host show topics, audience demographics, and past guest performance, then automatically surfaces the best-fit guests from a growing database. Hosts get higher-quality episodes with better guest-host chemistry, leading to improved listener engagement and episode downloads. Guests benefit by being matched with shows in their niche where they'll reach their ideal audience, creating real networking and visibility opportunities. The outcome: hosts save 10+ hours per week on guest sourcing and see measurable improvements in episode quality and listener retention.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"Founder has 8+ years of experience in podcast production and audio tech, having worked with 50+ independent creators and understanding the guest-sourcing pain point firsthand. Early beta users report 60% reduction in time spent finding guests and 35% increase in episode downloads after using the platform. Friend of the Pod has already facilitated 1,000+ successful host-guest matches with a 92% satisfaction rate. The platform was featured in Podcast Magazine's 'Tools to Watch' and has partnerships with three major podcast networks. Founder's personal mission: democratize podcast growth by removing friction from content creation, so creators can focus on what they do best—making great shows.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01UPtnZGqCZM3GFYaQYXnd3v\"}]}],\"system\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n        The process consists of 3 steps:\\n        1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n        2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n        3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            If the user has indicated they are finished brainstorming or ready to move on, \\n            just call the finishedTool.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"Podcast hosts at growing independent shows (10K-500K monthly listeners) who spend 5-15 hours per week manually searching for guests through email, Twitter, and LinkedIn. They're frustrated by the time investment, inconsistent guest quality, and the difficulty of finding niche experts who align with their audience. Their goal is to produce consistent, high-quality episodes without the administrative burden of guest sourcing, so they can focus on content creation and audience growth. Current solutions (email outreach, Facebook groups, generic guest databases) are slow, impersonal, and result in poor fits.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"Founder has 8+ years of experience in podcast production and audio tech, having worked with 50+ independent creators and understanding the guest-sourcing pain point firsthand. Early beta users report 60% reduction in time spent finding guests and 35% increase in episode downloads after using the platform. Friend of the Pod has already facilitated 1,000+ successful host-guest matches with a 92% satisfaction rate. The platform was featured in Podcast Magazine's 'Tools to Watch' and has partnerships with three major podcast networks. Founder's personal mission: democratize podcast growth by removing friction from content creation, so creators can focus on what they do best—making great shows.\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod eliminates the 'needle in a haystack' problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. The platform analyzes host show topics, audience demographics, and past guest performance, then automatically surfaces the best-fit guests from a growing database. Hosts get higher-quality episodes with better guest-host chemistry, leading to improved listener engagement and episode downloads. Guests benefit by being matched with shows in their niche where they'll reach their ideal audience, creating real networking and visibility opportunities. The outcome: hosts save 10+ hours per week on guest sourcing and see measurable improvements in episode quality and listener retention.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}"
          },
